The paper is about knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model, OrbitE, is a machine learning model that aims to improve the accuracy of knowledge graph embedding, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods in expressing true facts accurately, which relates to natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with the representation of entities and relations, which is a fundamental problem in databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed model in predicting missing facts, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR).
